regulatory.title: Derailment - Illinois & Midland Railroad Inc. near PEKIN, IL
regulatory.summary: Incident on 2025-11-30: 0 fatalities, 0 injuries. Estimated damage: $169384
regulatory.content: BNSF DELIVERED A LOADED COAL TRAIN INTO CRESCENT 2 POWERTON YARD. AT APPROX. 1830, THE TRAIN HAD GONE INTO EMERGENCY AND THE BNSF CREW INFORMED THE IMRR DISPATCHER. AFTER INVESTIGATION, THE TRAIN HADDERAILED 5 CARS ON THE NORTH END OF CRESCENT YARD. IMRR CHOSE E64C DUE TO THE CONDITION OF THE WHEELFLANGE BEING VERTICAL AND THE SWITCH POINT BEING A SAMPSON POINT AND STOCK RAIL WHICH TUCKS THE POINT UNDER THE STOCK RAIL. ADDITIONALLY, THE CAR, CAEG 826082, WHICH WAS THE LEAD CAR THAT DERAILED, AND THE LEADING WHEEL, L04, THE SUSPECT WHEEL, HAD AN OPEN WHEEL PROFILE DETECTED WHEEL ALERT IN RAILINC EQUIPMENT HEALTH MANAGEMENT SYSTEM FOR FLANGE THICKNESS. WHILE THE FLANGE THICKNESS WAS NOT AT ACONDEMNABLE LEVEL, IT WAS WORN AND SUSPECTED TO HAVE CLIMBED BASED ON ALL THE INFORMATION GATHEREDFROM THE INVESTIGATION. THE SWITCH POINT HAD A SMALL CHIP THAT APPEARED TO BE FROM THE WHEEL ONCE ITGOT ON TOP OF THE POINT. BNSF REPORTS $74,999 IN EQUIPMENT COSTS.

regulatory.title: Derailment - Norfolk Southern Railway Company near NORTH KANSAS CITY, MO
regulatory.summary: Incident on 2025-11-30: 0 fatalities, 0 injuries. Estimated damage: $22207
regulatory.content: D44D329 WAS PULLING EAST OUT OF TRACK 37 WITH 39 CARS TO START SWITCHING OPERATIONS.  THE TRAIN PULLED ABOUT 24 CARS PAST THE 55 SWITCH BEFORE THEY STARTED SHOVING BACK TO TRACK 46.  6 LOADED CARS (LINES 16-21) DERAILED DURING THE SHOVE MOVE ON THE 55 SWITCH. THERE WERE NO INJURIES.

regulatory.title: Other impacts - CANADIAN NATIONAL RAILWAY near HARVEY, IL
regulatory.summary: Incident on 2025-11-29: 0 fatalities, 0 injuries. Estimated damage: $38413
regulatory.content: THE CREW OF Q19851-24 WAS SHOVING A CUT OF CARS THROUGH EM09 TO SPOT EM03. CONDUCTOR FAILED TO LINETHE EM09/EM10 SWITCH RESULTING IN THE SWITCH BEING RAN THROUGH. CONDUCTOR DIDNT KNOW HE RAN THE SWITCH AND AFTER THEY DROPPED A CUT OF CARS OFF IN EM03 THEY STARTED TO PULL FORWARD CAUSING A CAR (DTTX760669) TO PICK THE RUN THROUGH SWITCH DERAILING THE CAR. ONCE THE CAR DERAILED IT TRAVELED APPROXIMATELY 600FT AND SIDESWIPED THE SOUTH CAR IN EM10 (DTTX781088) AND CAME TO A STOP.

regulatory.title: Other (describe in narrative) - Brightline Train near HALLANDALE, FL
